verbose_text: OCG requires the differentiation cytokine RANKL to bind to its receptor RANK, resulting in the intracellular RANK-TRAF6 interaction and subsequent activation of the transcription factors, NF-kappaB and activator protein 1 (AP-1) (consisting of c-fos and c-jun).
evidence: activation of the transcription factors, NF-kappaB and activator protein 1
